Class Library

java.lang.Object
Library
public class Library
extends java.lang.Object
An abstract data type that represents a Library where Book objects are stored and managed. Each library contains a "bag" (Book array) to hold books added and keeps track of the number of books.

    • Library

      public Library()
      Default constructor to create an empty bag.

  • Method Details

    • getNumBooks

      public int getNumBooks()
      Getter method to get the number of books in the library
      Returns:
      int of number of books in the bag

    • add

      public void add​(Book book)
      Adds a new book to the books array. If the books array is full, grow will be called to increase the array capacity by 4.
      Parameters:
      book - new book to be added

    • remove

      public boolean remove​(Book book)
      Removes a book from the books array. Shifts all books after the removed slot to the left (so that no gap exists between any two books).
      Parameters:
      book - book to be removed
      Returns:
      true if book was successfully removed, false if book does not exist

    • checkOut

      public boolean checkOut​(Book book)
      Checks out a book from the bag. Sets checkedOut field of Book to true if not already checked out (true).
      Parameters:
      book - book that will be checked out
      Returns:
      true if checked out successfully, false if already checked out or book does not exist

    • returns

      public boolean returns​(Book book)
      Returns a checked out book to the bag. Sets checkedOut field of Book to false if checked out.
      Parameters:
      book - book that will be returned
      Returns:
      true if book returned successfully, false if not checked out or book does not exist

    • printStandard

      public void printStandard()
      Print the list of books in the bag according to current sequence.

    • printByDate

      public void printByDate()
      Print the list of books by datePublished (ascending).

    • printByNumber

      public void printByNumber()
      Print the list of books by number (ascending).

    • bookData

      public Book bookData​(java.lang.String serialNumber)
      Getting the Book object given its serial number.
      Parameters:
      serialNumber - serial number of the book
      Returns:
      Book object with given serial number if found, otherwise returns empty Book
